:[{"name":"Lechtenberg","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Fritz.","Americanized form of German   Lichtenberg  ."]},{"name":"Lichtenberger","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Bernd, Dieter, Horst, Kurt.","German: habitational name for someone from any of numerous places called   Lichtenberg  ."]}]},{"name":"Bertha","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of a Continental Germanic name, a short form of various compound women's personal names derived from <i>berht</i> ‘famous’ (akin to Modern English <i>bright</i>). It probably existed in England before the Conquest, and was certainly reinforced by Norman use, but fell out of use in the 15th century. It was reintroduced into the English-speaking world from Germany in the 19th century, but has once again gone out of fashion."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Von","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Simplified spelling of   John   or a short form of   Jonathan .  The name is borne by the Canadian singer  Jon Vickers  (  b. 1926 ) and the American actor  Jon Voight  (  b. 1938 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Jonathan","meanings":["Biblical name, meaning ‘God has given’, composed of the same elements as those of   Matthew  , but in reverse order. This is the name of several characters in the Bible, most notably a son of King Saul, who was a devoted friend and supporter of the young David, even when David and Saul were themselves at loggerheads (1 Samuel 31; 2 Samuel 1:19–26). The name is often taken as symbolic of steadfast friendship and loyalty. Well-known bearers of the name include the Irish clergyman and writer  Jonathan Swift  (  1667-1745 ), British theatre director  Jonathan Miller  (  b. 1934 ), British actor  Jonathan Pryce  (  b. 1947 ), and British television presenter  Jonathan Ross  (  b. 1960 )."]},{"name":"Jonn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jon   or  <b>John</b> ."]},{"name":"John","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Bertha Von Lichtenberg was born about 1165, in Lichtenberg, Dieburg, Hesse, Germany. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Dieter lll von Katzenelenbogen. She died in 1220, at the age of 56."},"et":{"ABT 1165–1220":"umbes 1165–1220","1160–1219":"1160–1219","1192–1245":"1192–1245","1195–1253":"1195–1253","1202–1232":"1202–1232","1165–1220":"1165–1220","about 1192":"umbes 1192","1165":"1165","ABT 1202":"umbes 1202","1220":"1220","1253":"1253","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1192":"1192","about 1219":"umbes 1219","ABT 1165":"umbes 1165","1202":"1202","1245":"1245","1232":"1232","ABT    1195":"umbes 1195","1219":"1219","Katzenelnbogen, Unterlahnkreis, Hesse-Nassau, Prussia, Germany":"Katzenelnbogen, Unterlahnkreis, Hessen-Nassau, Freistaat Preußen, Saksamaa","Starkenburg, Hesse-Darmstadt, Prussia, Germany":"Starkenburg, Großherzogtum Hessen, Deutsches Reich","Of Lichtenberg, Starkenburg, Hesse-Darmstadt":"Lichtenberg, Kreis Dieburg, Hessen, Saksamaa","Katzenelnbogen, Unterlahnkreis, Hessen-Nassau, Preußen, Deutschland":"Katzenelnbogen, Rhein-Lahn-Kreis, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Of Katzenelnboge,H-Nss,Prss":"Hessen-Nassau, Preußen, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"ABT 1165–1220":"noin 1165–1220","1160–1219":"1160–1219","1192–1245":"1192–1245","1195–1253":"1195–1253","1202–1232":"1202–1232","1165–1220":"1165–1220","about 1192":"noin 1192","1165":"1165","ABT 1202":"noin 1202","1220":"1220","1253":"1253","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1192":"1192","about 1219":"noin 1219","ABT 1165":"noin 1165","1202":"1202","1245":"1245","1232":"1232","ABT    1195":"noin 1195","1219":"1219","Katzenelnbogen, Unterlahnkreis, Hesse-Nassau, Prussia,